														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2457464">
									

<p>This has a very strong hook - a team that doesn't need to fear death or injury, but isn't quite human, is interesting psychological territory - and the writing is clearer than the draft I read (or perhaps I just read it more carefully the second time).</p>
<p>I think I'm stuck at a no-vote for now. Partly because some of the body horror isn't quite clicking with me at the moment (although my tastes may change on that), partly because some of the build-up here feels very withholding (eg the stuff about the book) and partly because while I know the interchangeability of the characters is part of the point, that doesn't make them more interesting. Some hints of individual personalities would have helped, I think.</p>

							</div>

								
					
