			<div class="content" id="post-content-2458623">
									

<p>I can remedy some of those issues:</p>
<p>The italics section is an origin story of sorts, detailing the original creation of the MTF. It shows four nameless test subjects uploading their minds into a computer to be re-downloaded into grown bodies, experiencing their post-human lives being experimented on, getting their minds erased by the destruction of the facility, and their rediscovery by the Foundation.</p>
<p>The machinery nullifies the &quot;meatgrinder&quot; effect occurring in the farmhouse, allowing the MTF to enter and conduct operations without being turned into pulpy masses of cancer. However, its volatility (read: tendency to explode violently) means that the nonfeeling, respawning MTF is the only group allowed to actually use it.</p>
<p>The book&#8230; well that's foreshadowing.</p>

